{"cursor":"7644","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"{{Infobox road |country = USA |name = Texarkana Loop |marker_image = |length_mi\n= 16 |established = |direction_a = CCW |direction_b = CW |terminus_a = W. of\nTexarkana |terminus_b = |junction =     \n E. of Texarkana |browse = |system =  }}\n\n:\"I-130\" redirects here. [http://www.uscis.gov/portal/site/uscis/menuitem.5af9b-\n:b95919f35e66f614176543f6d1a/?vgnextoid=c67c7f9ded54d010VgnVCM10000048f3d6a1RCRD\n:I-130] is also a United States immigration form to petition for an alien\n:relative.\n\nThe 'Loop' is a beltway around Texarkana, a twin city in the U.S. states of\nArkansas and Texas, running about 16 miles (26 km). Consisting of 'Highway\n245' - sometimes called 'Loop 245' - in Arkansas, and 'Loop 151' and a section\nof U.S. Highway 59 in Texas, it forms a three-quarter loop around the east,\nsouth and west sides of the city. (Interstate 30 completes the circle on the\nnorth side.) Except for a portion of Highway 245 where it meets I-30 at a\ndiamond interchange east of Texarkana, the Loop is built to freeway standards.\n\nThe south side is bisected by State Line Avenue, which runs northâsouth along\nthe state line. The whole half in Arkansas is Highway 245; US 59 intersects the\nLoop near the southwest corner, and so only the south side in Texas is Loop 151.\nOld US 59 into Texarkana - Lake Drive - is now State Highway 93.\n","linknr":274,"url":"Loop_(Texarkana)","recorded":1362564914,"links":46,"instances":["mo","arkansas","arkansas","geographical_proximity","texas","texas","texas","arkansas","texas","nhs"],"pdf":["http://cms.transportation.org/sites/route/docs/2000%20USRN_Cmte.pdf","http://www.arkansashighways.com/ARRA/ARRA%20List%20AHTD%20WEB.pdf"],"categories":["Freeways in the United States","Interstate 49|Texarkana","Beltways in the United States|Texarkana","Texarkana|Loop","U.S. Route 59"],"headings":["Route description","Exit list","References"],"image":["//upload.wikimedia.org/wiki